For me, it is a year of changes.
I don't want to feed the tech giants with my money, data, and energy. Or coaches who have their own extroverted solution and try to sell it to everyone. I am on the lookout for new ways to run my business, and at the same time, I am fighting against my long-held belief that one must do things in a certain way to achieve success.
The English translation of "Wünscht mir Glück!" is "Wish me luck!"
The first steps I have already taken.
I have canceled my Facebook account, removed all Meta and Pinterest trackers from my website, and deleted my private WhatsApp account.
Yesterday, I also removed Google Analytics, the last external tracker, from my website, and I feel good about it.
Recently, I have subscribed to a European CRM to have better DSGVO support, and will be moving my business in that direction over the next few weeks.
I have transferred my MX account to Proton and now have full SPF, DKIM, and DMARC without having to pay anything to Google for normal email validation.
